              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Tencent shares drop after military blacklist</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Tencent shares fell nearly 10% after the US Defense Department labeled it a <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-07-01-2025-h2-2-chinese-military-entity" target="_blank">Chinese military entity</a>. The designation doesn’t impose sanctions but discourages US firms from trading with such companies. Tencent denies military ties and vows to work with the Pentagon to clarify its position. Tencent’s stock has been resilient amid China’s slowdown, but this development could affect investor confidence. Some Chinese firms, including Xiaomi, have successfully fought similar designations.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

